description.plain:
SHAED is a head­bobbing pop project formed in 2011 in Washington, D.C. The group consists of multi­instrumentalist twin brothers Max and Spencer Ernst and powerhouse vocalist Chelsea Lee. Lee’s vocals weave divinely through the Ernst twin’s pop­sensible production that can make anyone move.

SHAED’s debut EP, Just Wanna See, was released on September 9, 2016.

Their highly anticipated debut album, High Dive, was released on May 14, 2021. It featured their smash hit “Trampoline” as well as ZAYN’s remix of the hit. “Trampoline” and its remix was accompanied by 3 singles, and 7 other tracks.

songs.title: Trampoline

description.plain:
The song is most recognizable from the Apple commercial in late October 2018 for the MacBook Air.

https://youtu.be/G7iI7YmIr30

In an interview with Pop Dust on July 23rd, 2018, Chelsea Lee answered two questions about to “Trampoline.” She said that the band was simply trying to write a great song, and “Trampoline” was a build-up from working in a studio every day.

The idea behind the song was inspired by watching a home video of Max and Spencer Ernst (both are band members) jumping on a trampoline. They wanted to tell a story that played along with their surrounding environment outside of their home. This story was focused around the idea of the “Upside Down” (a Stranger Things reference), and they wanted the plot to be similar to Alice In Wonderland.

songs.title: Melt

description.plain: There was a time in my life when I felt like I had no control over the art I was creating. I was pressured to sing and act a certain way and I felt totally lost. I eventually realized what was happening and Max and Spencer were there to help me through it.
